{"TopicId":216735,"ForumId":198,"TopicTitle":"The docking port is embedded/placed inside the craft parts","CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-19T20:32:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-19T20:32:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe docking ports are embedded inside the craft, which causes subsequent bugs, undocking problems, and RUDs. Docking ports are much more wobbly than other parts, under different influences they behave like springs. After speeding up time and loading saves, they almost always end up located inside parts. Below you can see an example of this bug, where the ports are embedded in the craft (under spoiler)\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022d46KerbalSpaceProgram21.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://u.cubeupload.com/Vortygont/d46KerbalSpaceProgram21.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here is video, where you can see typical behaviour of docking ports\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/u_A0RIadF4Q?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022[0.1.2.0] Docking ports wobbly behaviour\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-01T04:49:05Z\u0022 title=\u002206/01/2023 04:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 1, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Little 908","CreatedById":228185,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-19T20:45:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, wa\u2026 what were the devs even thinking while coding in the docking ports? Like they are like ksp 1s docking ports, but somehow they managed to make them more? springy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:13px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://media4.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExYjM2YmE3YmM2OWIzYjgwOWE4YTU5YTllNDI5MmE1ZmRlY2RjY2Q4OSZjdD1n/DcFTHr2zKHL2Q5T6mI/giphy.gif\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Animated GIF\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 style=\u0022border-style:none;vertical-align:middle;\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 src=\u0022https://media4.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExYjM2YmE3YmM2OWIzYjgwOWE4YTU5YTllNDI5MmE1ZmRlY2RjY2Q4OSZjdD1n/DcFTHr2zKHL2Q5T6mI/giphy.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:13px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ffffff;\u0022\u003EI think they put suspension inside the docking ports\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-19T20:49:49Z\u0022 title=\u002204/19/2023 08:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 19, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Little 908\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-19T21:30:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224274633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216735\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681936344\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223549\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vortygont\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, Vortygont said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe docking ports are embedded inside the craft, which causes subsequent bugs, undocking problems, and RUDs. Docking ports are much more wobbly than other parts, under different influences they behave like springs. After speeding up time and loading saves, they almost always end up located inside parts. Below you can see an example of this bug, where the ports are embedded in the craft (under spoiler)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe docking ports can end up inside other parts because KSP2 locks stressed parts positions when timewarp is engaged:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6898547508\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/214823-permanent-part-drift-is-happening-because-time-warp-is-saving-stressed-parts-coordinates-into-memory/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}